  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted across the 5 flow-speed operating points; Latin hypercube sampling over 12 geometric and boundary-condition parameters confirmed that relative hemolysis index remained below the RH < 1 threshold at the 95th percentile. Detailed UQ results are summarised in the validation report narrative; structured sensitivity-analysis metadata is incorporated within the validation evidence record.",
